# .cursorrules 파일 내용 (프로젝트 루트)

## Project Guidelines

### Technology Stack
- Frontend: React 18, TypeScript, React Hooks
- Backend: Node.js, Express, MongoDB
- UI Library: Recharts for charts
- Design System: CSS custom properties (--color-*, --space-*, etc.)

### Code Style
- Use arrow functions instead of function declarations
- Prefer const/let over var
- Use destructuring for object/array assignments
- Keep components under 300 lines
- Extract custom hooks for complex logic

### Accessibility Standards
- WCAG 2.1 AA compliance required
- Color contrast minimum 4.5:1 for normal text
- All form inputs must have labels
- Keyboard navigation must work (Tab, Enter, Escape)
- Add ARIA labels where appropriate

### Testing Requirements
- Unit tests for utility functions
- Component tests using React Testing Library
- Minimum 70% code coverage
- Test file naming: [filename].test.ts(x)

### Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (DashboardCard.tsx)
- Utilities: camelCase (formatDate.ts)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (API_BASE_URL)
- Props interfaces: Component name + "Props" (DashboardCardProps)

### File Structure
src/
├── components/ # React components
├── hooks/ # Custom React hooks
├── utils/ # Utility functions
├── types/ # TypeScript types/interfaces
├── services/ # API services
├── context/ # React Context
└── styles/ # Global styles

### Performance Standards
- Component render time < 16ms (60fps)
- API calls debounced/throttled where appropriate
- Images lazy-loaded
- Bundle size monitored

### Documentation
- Add JSDoc comments for public functions
- Document component props with TypeScript
- Include usage examples in complex components

